text: Keilira is a genus of Australian huntsman spiders that was first described by D. B. Hirst in 1989. it contains two species, found in South Australia and Victoria: K. sokoli and K. sparsomaculata. ==See also== * List of Sparassidae species ==References== Category:Araneomorphae genera Category:Sparassidae Category:Spiders of Australia
title: Keilira
